{"title": "Lost Despatch", "description": "A story constructed with Washington as the central locus, and with the web of circumstance weaving itself around Miss Nancy Newton, a rebel spy who falls into danger through the strange disappearance of an important despatch. Miss Newton, made to swear allegiance to the Confederacy by her dying father, acts as a bearer of secret information to Richmond. Loved by a Union officer, Major Robert Goddard, she finds herself in a distressing predicament upon her arrest under the double and sinister charge of treason and murder. (Summary by Boston Transcript quoted in The Book review Digest Ninth Annual Compilation, 1913)\r\n\r\nPlease note that certain epithets used may be considered offensive to modern readers.", "duration": 23223, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2856", "name": "Natalie Sumner Lincoln"}], "coverArt": null, "copyright_year": "1913", "genres": ["Suspense", "Espionage", "Political & Thrillers"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "James R. Hedrick"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "James R. Hedrick"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "DaveC"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "mleigh"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Pigeon's Flight", "readers": [16205], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/lostdespatch_2603_librivox/lostdespatch_01_lincoln_64kb.mp3", "duration": 549}, {"section": 2, "title": "Brains vs. Brawn", "readers": [16205], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/lostdespatch_2603_librivox/lostdespatch_02_lincoln_64kb.mp3", "duration": 775}, {"section": 3, "title": "A Knot of Ribbon Blue", "readers": [16205], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/lostdespatch_2603_librivox/lostdespatch_03_lincoln_64kb.mp3", "duration": 829}, {"section": 4, "title": "Banquo's Ghost", "readers": [16205], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/lostdespatch_2603_librivox/lostdespatch_04_lincoln_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1216}, {"section": 5, "title": "A Scrap of Paper", "read